t because they're frightened or in any kind of real danger, let alone unusual circumstances.and so forth... writing about the film falls short of the experience of actually seeing it. but please, please, save yourself the bother, even if your morbid curiosity is piqued! the film is so bad it can't even be enjoyed as unintentional humor (versus, say, king vidor's "solomon & sheeba" starring yul brynner wearing a wig). life is too short to waste watching such nonsense. there must be something more productive and enjoyable to do, like walking the dog or cleaning a birdcage.

